Subject: [PATCH] unity(harness): back-port comms-hold mode into canonical
 DclPlaytestHarness
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Adds the live multi-client "comms" mode that was authored in the win11 checkout's
DclHarness drop during the 3-platform comms test, into the rig CANONICAL source so
every platform's harness drop carries it (was drifted — drop had it, canonical didn't):
- RunCommsHoldFromMenu / mode "comms" dispatch
- RunCommsHoldCoroutine: join -> GP(0,0) -> HOLD (no teleport-away/realm-switch/exit),
  logs remote-avatar census + refreshes a world shot every CENSUS_S
- CountWorldAvatars(out names): non-preview AvatarBase census (remote = total-1)

Purely additive (+129). Platform-agnostic. Local only, no push.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>
Claude-Session: https://claude.ai/code/session_014nh2TNCVS9LzKhzTM3DD34
---
 unity/DclPlaytestHarness.cs | 129 ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
 1 file changed, 129 insertions(+)

